 Centane - Centane police are looking for a missing 76-year-old man Gongo Xulashe. "He was last seen on Tuesday, at about 04:45, as he was leaving his home at Teko Springs Village, Centane," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "He was on his way to Butterworth Hospital where he was going to get ambulance to Frere Hospital in East London. "He is dark in complexion. He was wearing khaki jacket, black trouser, light blue shirt and grey hat. "Centane Police with assistance of the community have been looking for him with negative results." Anyone who can assist Centane Police is kindly requested to contact them at 047 498 1096 or 073 288 0340. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 